HEADWORD: Palatine Hill
<hw>Palatine Hill</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧l"⟦adot⟧*t⟦imac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>prop.
n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Mons Palatinus</ets>, It. <ets>Monte
Palatino</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of the "seven hills" of Rome, situated
southeast of the Capitoline and north-northeast of the Aventine. It
borders on the Roman Forum; is the traditional seat of the city founded
by Romulus; was the seat of private and later of imperial residences;
and contains many antiquities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Century Dict., 1906</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palative</ent>⟦br⟧
